body: Update: The exact same problem is present in ONNX Runtime 1.6.0.
Update: The problem persists in ONNX Runtime 1.7.0 with DML 1.4.2.

@j-paulus Sorry this got buried in the notification noise - I'm cleaning up old issues. :/ I was able to repro seeing a C++ `Ort::Exception::Exception` with ORT 1.10 via the value 768 on Nvidia Quadro P400 (thanks for the repro snippets). The `output_tensors` is size 1, but the contained `Ort::Value` is empty. After enabling the debug layer via dxcpl.exe...

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1809166/156119505-35cef5b0-6b0c-4caa-ac3d-194540898f8e.png)

...I saw the following output:

```
D3D12 ERROR: ID3D12Device::RemoveDevice: Device removal has been triggered for the following reason
DXGI_ERROR_DEVICE_HUNG: The Device took an unreasonable amount of time to execute its commands, or the hardware crashed/hung.
As a result, the TDR (Timeout Detection and Recovery) mechanism has been triggered.
The current Device Context was executing commands when the hang occurred.
The application may want to respawn and fallback to less aggressive use of the display hardware).
[ EXECUTION ERROR #232: DEVICE_REMOVAL_PROCESS_AT_FAULT]
```

I suspect the ConvTranspose is taking too long.

issue.title: Exception in DirectML on second inference run

labels.name: ep:DML
labels.description: issues related to the DirectML execution provider

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Hi,
**Describe the bug**
I run a 3D UNet with the C onnxruntime and DML. The first time Run is called, everything works as expected. But on the second call, an Exception is raised immediately. This only happens if DML is enabled, and the NVIDIA GPU is selected (I also have an intel). I slightly modified the fns_candy_style_transfer example project to test this model. If needed, I can upload that here (I just need to tidy it up first). I compiled the onnxruntime from master and also checked that the correct DirectML.dll is loaded.

**Urgency**
Medium urgency

**System information**
- OS Platform: Windows 10 21H1
- ONNX Runtime installed from source
- ONNX Runtime version: master (bfb20b315d9763f4113fdb1b15444626d66874e6)
- Visual Studio version: 2019 (16.11.8)
- GPU model and memory: Intel HD Graphics 630 + NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1050 with 4GB

**To Reproduce**
Load this model
[onnxruntime_dml_bug_test.zip](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/files/8062687/onnxruntime_dml_bug_test.zip)
and run inference with all zeros two times. It crashes on the second run.

**Expected behavior**
No crash
